cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, as it introduces a new measure to evaluate the transferability of learned representations for classifiers. It also mentions the use of deep neural networks and the ImageNet and CIFAR100 datasets, which are commonly used in these sub-fields. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories, as it discusses the effectiveness of the proposed measure in predicting the performance and convergence speed of transfer and meta-transfer learning methods, even for small or imbalanced data.
